{"id":82427,"date":"2022-06-05T10:24:20","date_gmt":"2022-06-05T08:24:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=82427"},"modified":"2022-06-09T18:13:43","modified_gmt":"2022-06-09T16:13:43","slug":"montepulciano-italy","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/italy\/montepulciano-italy\/","title":{"rendered":"Best Things to do in Montepulciano, Italy"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"todo\">Things to do in Montepulciano, Italy<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Montepulciano, Italy, is small but perfectly formed; it doesn&#x2019;t have many activities or museums, but it&#x2019;s the ideal place to relax with a glass of wine as you look over the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/italy\/tuscany\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tuscan<\/a> countryside. True to its name (&#x2018;Monte&#x2019; means &#x2018;Mountain&#x2019;), Montepulciano sits on a ridge over 600 meters above sea level.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133122\/Montepulciano-italy-5.jpg\" alt=\"Montepulciano tuscany italy\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Montepulciano tuscany italy\" class=\"wp-image-82784 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133122\/Montepulciano-italy-5.jpg 1281w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133122\/Montepulciano-italy-5-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133122\/Montepulciano-italy-5-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133122\/Montepulciano-italy-5-226x338.jpg 226w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-