t\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133136\/Montepulciano-italy-1.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>Start at one of the entry gates into the Historic Center (&#x2018;Centro Storico&#x2019;), either Porta al Prato or the Porta Delle Farine (the two main gates). From here, wander up the II Corso, a beautiful uphill street that takes you through town. Make sure to stop and admire the beautiful houses lived in by some of the wealthiest families in Montepulciano throughout the ages. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stop and have a coffee (or two!) on your way as you browse the artisan shops selling ceramics, art, jewelry, and homemade food.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3.jpg\" alt=\"Montepulciano restaurants\"><\/noscript><img width=\"237\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Montepulciano restaurants\" class=\"wp-image-82778 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1349px) 100vw, 1349px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3.jpg 1349w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3-422x600.jpg 422w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3-569x810.jpg 569w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3-237x338.jpg 237w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3-21x30.jpg 21w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3-115x163.jpg 115w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/21133044\/Montepulciano-italy-3-126x180.jpg 126w, https:\/\/stati